knowledge-path-flesh-s1-name = Principle of Hunger
knowledge-path-flesh-s1-desc =
    Opens up the Path of Flesh to you.
    Allows you to transmute a knife and a pool of blood into a Bloody Blade.
knowledge-path-flesh-s1-flavor =
    "Hundreds of us starved, but not me... I found strength in my greed."

knowledge-path-flesh-s2-name = Grasp of Flesh
knowledge-path-flesh-s2-desc =
    Your Mansus Grasp gains the ability to create Ghouls from corpses.
    Ghouls look like corpses to heathens' eyes and typically only have 50 health, but can use Bloody Blades effectively.
    This ability is highly visible to those around you.
knowledge-path-flesh-s2-flavor =
    "That particular taste, which was neither fair nor foul, drove me to greater and greater hunger."

knowledge-path-flesh-s3-name = Imperfect Recipe
knowledge-path-flesh-s3-desc =
    Allows you to transmute a humanoid corpse and a poppy to create a Voiceless Dead.
    Voiceless Dead are mute Ghouls, who typically only have 100 health, but can use Bloody Blades effectively.
knowledge-path-flesh-s3-flavor =
    "I found a certain recipe, unfinished... yet still, I pushed forward."

knowledge-path-flesh-s4-name = Mark of Flesh
knowledge-path-flesh-s4-desc =
    Your Mansus Grasp now applies the Mark of Flesh. The mark is triggered from an attack with your Bloody Blade.
    When triggered, its target begins to bleed heavily, before jumping to a new target.
knowledge-path-flesh-s4-flavor =
    "I knew myself to be marked. The Wasting Doe spoke to me in my dreams."

knowledge-path-flesh-s5-name = Knitting of Flesh
knowledge-path-flesh-s5-desc =
    Grants you the spell Knit Flesh. This spell causes a random effect to its target, between blinding, muting, and causing the target to vomit profusely.
    This spell also allows you to heal your servants, with a long do-after.
    This spell requires a Focus to cast.
knowledge-path-flesh-s5-flavor =
    "It taught me the secrets of taste. Its pleasures, its torments, the particular savors which could influence the world outside my dreams."

knowledge-path-flesh-s6-name = Raw Ritual
knowledge-path-flesh-s6-desc =
    Allows you to transmute a pair of eyes, a stomach, and a pool of blood to create a Raw Prophet.
    Raw Prophets can jaunt, have the ability to link minds to communicate with ease, and have a powerful laser eye, which can burn your opponents.
knowledge-path-flesh-s6-flavor =
    "I could not continue alone. I had met the Prophets in my walks through the wood. They led me to become a part of something greater."

knowledge-path-flesh-s7-name = Bleeding Steel
knowledge-path-flesh-s7-desc =
    Your Bloody Blade now causes enemies to bleed heavily on attack, even more so when combined with your Mark of Flesh.
knowledge-path-flesh-s7-flavor =
    "They led me to a field of rot and bone.
    I finally began to understand. And then, blood rained from the heavens."

knowledge-path-flesh-s8-name = Lonely Ritual
knowledge-path-flesh-s8-desc =
    Allows you to transmute a heart, a stomach, lungs and a pen to create a Stalker.
    Stalkers can jaunt, release EMPs, and are overall strong in combat.
knowledge-path-flesh-s8-flavor =
    "I was able to combine my hunger and desires to summon a fury of sinew and bone.
    An ever shapeshifting mass of flesh, it knew well my goals. The Doe approved."

knowledge-path-flesh-s9-name = Priest’s Final Hymn
knowledge-path-flesh-s9-desc =
    The Ascension ritual of the Path of Flesh.
    Bring 4 corpses to a Transmutation Rune to complete the ritual.
    When completed, you gain the ability to shed your human form and become the Lord of the Night, a supremely powerful creature.
    While in the Lord of the Night form, you can consume the living to heal and are able to devour walls and airlocks alike, much like a Space Dragon.
    Your melee attacks in this form are very powerful, doing a large amount of blunt damage, and being able to hit many targets at once.
